docs.abstract: Broadcom’s takeover bid for Qualcomm may now be in jeopardy because of a little-known committee that can essentially kill multibillion-dollar global deals.
docs.snippet: Broadcom’s takeover bid for Qualcomm may now be in jeopardy because of a little-known committee that can essentially kill multibillion-dollar global deals.
docs.lead_paragraph: Qualcomm, one of the world’s largest chip makers, has spent the last four months fending off a hostile takeover from Broadcom, a Singaporean rival. The fate of the proposed takeover may now be in jeopardy because of a little-known committee of top administration officials who meet in secret, wielding power to kill the biggest multibillion-dollar global deals.

headline.main: Cfius, Powerful and Unseen, Is a Gatekeeper on Major Deals
headline.print_headline: How Cfius Rides Herd  On Major Global Deals

docs.abstract: Walmart is raising hourly wages by $300 million, just a sliver of what it could save through tax cuts. But it’s a wonder Walmart can get away with so little.
docs.snippet: Walmart is raising hourly wages by $300 million, just a sliver of what it could save through tax cuts. But it’s a wonder Walmart can get away with so little.
docs.lead_paragraph: Walmart’s pay increase, purportedly inspired by the recent cut in the corporate tax rate, is a little less than real largess. The retailer’s extra spending on hourly wages is just a sliver of what it could save in taxes, though — and a tight labor market is likely to have been a more potent driver.

docs.abstract: An alliance over broker recruitment rules is falling apart as wealth management firms threaten legal action to stop departing advisers from taking clients with them.
docs.snippet: An alliance over broker recruitment rules is falling apart as wealth management firms threaten legal action to stop departing advisers from taking clients with them.
docs.lead_paragraph: When a financial adviser leaves a firm, clients often get caught in the middle of what amounts to a messy divorce. A squabble now playing out in the wealth management industry suggests that many of those splits could get messier.

headline.main: As Big Firms Exit Broker Pact, Investors Are Uneasy
headline.print_headline: As Big Firms Abandon Broker Pact, Investors Are Uneasy

docs.abstract: Two recent cases show that misstatements are not necessarily enough to prove securities fraud when sophisticated investors are involved.
docs.snippet: Two recent cases show that misstatements are not necessarily enough to prove securities fraud when sophisticated investors are involved.
docs.lead_paragraph: Proving a case of fraud seems easy: find a lie and show someone lost money because of it, or at least paid more than they should have. But in the trading of mortgage securities, a lie might not mean fraud.

headline.main: Can Sophisticated Investors Be Defrauded? Two Cases Raise Hurdles
